{"name": "vdk-plugin-control-cli", "metadata": {"name": "vdk-plugin-control-cli", "version": "0.1.1431637373", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/vmware/versatile-data-kit", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["vdk-core", "vdk-control-cli", "requests"], "summary": "Versatile Data Kit SDK plugin exposing CLI commands for managing the lifecycle of a Data Jobs.", "upload_time": 1724915980}, "documentation": ["<a href=\"https://pypistats.org/packages/vdk-plugin-control-cli\" alt=\"Monthly Downloads\">\n        <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/vdk-plugin-control-cli.svg\" alt=\"monthly download count for vdk-plugin-control-cli\"></a>\n\nThis plugin allows vdk-core to access vdk-control-cli functionality.\n\nUpon installing it enhances vdk with CLI commands for data job lifecycle management available from vdk-control-cli package\n\nIt will also install properties plugin and switch Properties in vdk to use Control Service Properties API.\nBy default no Properties backend is used otherwise.\n\n# Usage\n\n\n```bash\npip install vdk-plugin-control-cli\n```\n\n### New CLI commands\n\nThen on the vdk CLI you should be able to see the new commands. Run\n```bash\nvdk --help\n```\nand you will see extra commands being added:\n```\nCommands:\n  ...\n  login                  Authentication against the Control Service.\n  logout                 Logout the user from the Data Jobs Service by...\n  create                 Creates a new data job in cloud and locally.\n  delete                 Deletes a data job from the cloud.\n  deploy                 Deploys a data job.\n  ...\n```\n\nAnd you can use them from the same CLI `vdk`\n\n### New properties backend client registered\n\nYou can now access remote properties from Control Service Properties API\nStore state, configuration or secrets there using CLI or Python JobInput API\n\nFor example, let's store some api-uri\n\n```bash\nvdk properties --set 'api-uri' 'http://cool.cool.api.com'\n```\n\nand then we can use it in our data job\n\n```python\ndef run(job_input: IJobInput):\n    uri = job_input.get_property('api-uri')\n    print(requests.get(uri))\n```\n\n# Build\n\nThe easiest way is to use the ../build-plugin.sh helper script\n\n```bash\n../build-plugin.sh\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.properties_plugin", "documentation": ["Copyright 2023-2024 Broadcom", "SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0"], "functions": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.properties_plugin.initialize_job", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "context", "type": {"name": "JobContext", "xref": {"fqname": "vdk.internal.builtin_plugins.run.job_context.JobContext", "project": "vdk-core"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.properties_plugin.log", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.control_service_properties_client", "documentation": ["Copyright 2023-2024 Broadcom", "SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.control_service_properties_client.log", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.control_service_properties_client.ControlServicePropertiesServiceClient", "bases": ["IPropertiesServiceClient"], "methods": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.control_service_properties_client.ControlServicePropertiesServiceClient.__init__", "asynchronous