: {"fqname": "vdk.internal.core.config.ConfigurationBuilder", "project": "vdk-core"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.execution_skip.run_job", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "context", "type": {"name": "JobContext", "xref": {"fqname": "vdk.internal.builtin_plugins.run.job_context.JobContext", "project": "vdk-core"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.execution_skip.log", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.execution_skip.EXECUTION_SKIP_CHECKER_ENABLED", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.execution_skip.ConcurrentExecutionChecker", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.execution_skip.ConcurrentExecutionChecker.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rest_api_url", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.execution_skip.ConcurrentExecutionChecker.is_job_execution_running", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "job_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "job_team", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "job_execution_attempt_id", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["\\:param job_name : str value for the job name\n\\:param job_team : str value for the job team\n\\:param job_execution_attempt_id : str current job's execution id as returned by VDK execution_state\nThis method calls the \"/data-jobs/for-team/\\{team_name}/name/\\{job_name}/executions\"\nendpoint with the additional params \"submitted\" and \"running\". The API will return all jobs that are\nsubmitted and running with the provided team and job name. We have the following possible scenarios:\nAPI returns an empty list - this means no other data jobs excecutions are running and we can proceed with current execution.\nAPI returns one execution with a different ID - this means that another excecution is running and we should skip.\nAPI returns one job with the same ID - this means that we can proceed with excecution.\nAPI returns two jobs one of which has a different ID - we need to skip current excecution.\nIt then parses the response and returns a boolean.\n\\:return: bool\n\n> If the data job has a different execution running in K8S.\n> A running different execution means that there is a data job execution currently\n> submitted or running with a different id and in that case we should skip current execution\n> until the other finishes.\n"]}, {"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.execution_skip.ConcurrentExecutionChecker._get_running_job_executions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "job_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "team_name", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "DataJobExecution", "xref": {"fqname": "taurus_datajob_api.DataJobExecution", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["The class make sure to check if there is another execution of the data job already started.\nIt is used to prevent concurrent executions from getting started in the same time.\nAs often data jobs are not expected to be parallelizable since they do maintain state - for example\ningestion job that pulls data since last time it ran and moves it to a warehouse would duplicate it\nif started concurrently."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.control_service_api_error_decorator", "documentation": ["Copyright 2023-2024 Broadcom", "SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.control_service_api_error_decorator.log", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.control_service_api_error_decorator.ConstrolServiceApiErrorDecorator", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.control_service_api_error_decorator.ConstrolServiceApiErrorDecorator.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "what", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "consequences", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["---\nparam consequences: what are the consequences for the user (see VDK error standard).\nparam what: what is the error message (see VDK error standard). Will be set if exception\n  does not provide one.\n---\n\nWill be set if exception does not provide one.\n"]}, {"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.control_service_api_error_decorator.ConstrolServiceApiErrorDecorator._get_error", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exception", "type": {"name": "ApiException", "xref": {"fqname": "taurus_datajob_api.ApiException", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vdk.plugin.control_cli_plugin.control_service_api_error_decorator.ConstrolServiceApiErrorDecorator.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fn", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "ins